thread.title_full: Pakistan v England video: Shan Masood headbutts James Anderson delivery onto his stumps in first Test | The Advertiser

title: video: Shan Masood headbutts James Anderson delivery onto his stumps in
text:
IT’S unlikely England quick James Anderson will ever forget his 414th Test wicket.
When Anderson bowled Shan Masood in the first in Abu Dhabi it was significant for two reasons.
The first was because it drew Anderson level with swing king Wasim Akram as the tenth highest wicket-taker in Test history.
The second was because of the manner in which he bowled Masood, because the fact of the matter is the ball Anderson delivered had no right to end up clattering into the stumps.
Reeling away from a short delivery from the England quick, Masood got himself in a tangle and deflected the ball onto the stumps via his helmet.
It was far from the ideal start for Pakistan, leaving the side at 1-5 in the third over after electing to bat first.
England have their first wicket! Shan Masood taking his coach's advice to "use his head" a tad too literally there #PAKvENG
— England's Barmy Army (@TheBarmyArmy) October 13, 2015
Shan Masood bowled by Anderson. Excellent seam movement off the batsman's grille onto the stumps. But they all count.
— mike selvey (@selvecricket) October 13, 2015
Shan Masood bowled off the grill of the helmet turning the head. Not high up there on the acceptable dismissal list for an opening batsman.
— Simon Mann (@Cricket_Mann) October 13, 2015
